    <h1>Lazy Evaluation</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Abelson &amp; Sussman &middot; 1996 &middot; <a href="https://mitp-content-server.mit.edu/books/content/sectbyfn/books_pres_0/6515/sicp.zip/full-text/book/book-Z-H-27.html#%_sec_4.2">SICP &sect;4.2</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Normal-order evaluation delays arguments until needed. <strong>Thunks</strong> wrap unevaluated expressions with their environments. Memoization ensures each thunk is forced at most once.</p>
    </div>


