    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Python is strictly applicative-order, so laziness must be encoded explicitly via <code>lambda</code> wrappers or generators. Scheme's <code>delay</code>/<code>force</code> are macros that do the wrapping automatically. In a fully lazy evaluator (like Haskell), neither is needed &mdash; all arguments are thunks by default. The Python generator protocol (<code>yield</code>) provides a natural translation for streams but not for general lazy arguments.</p>

